name: 4-methoxy-3-nitrobenzamide

In this compound, 4-methoxy-3-nitrobenzamide, we have three functional groups that we need to consider: a methoxy group (-OCH3), a nitro group (-NO2), and an amide group (-CONH2). The nitro group is an electron-withdrawing group and can engage in intermolecular attractions which would significantly increase the melting point, estimated as +80 °C. Lastly, the amide group can engage in hydrogen bonding which greatly increases the melting point, estimated as +120 °C. The cumulative effect of these groups on benzene's base melting point should give a rough estimate of the compound's melting point.
